hopobject.body: How much will it cost to send this letter to ? vaseretic medscape Roseanne Barr was already a stand-up heavy hitter by the late '80s, but it was her turn as the loud-mouthed backbone of the Conner brood on 'Roseanne' that made her a household name. Barr went on to win both an Emmy and Golden Globe for portrayal of the crass, politically incorrect matriarch. These days Barr is back at it with her stand-up routine and recently released her third book, 'Roseannearchy: Dispatches from the Nut Farm.' The mother of five can only hope it's enough to erase the memory of her infamous 1990 national anthem performance.
